{"ts":"2026-06-06T21:49:05.632Z","author":"unknown","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/2","value":{"created_at":"2026-06-06T21:49:05.632Z","author":"unknown","text":"CodeQL follow-up evidence after merge:\n- After main-branch CodeQL completed, `gh api repos/unbraind/pm-cli/code-scanning/alerts?state=open&per_page=100` returned 10 open alerts (7 polynomial-redos, 1 biased cryptographic random, 2 bad-code-sanitization in test harness code).\n- Implemented targeted remediations instead of suppressing queries: unbiased ID token generation (`crypto.randomInt`), linear-time slug/tail parsers replacing flagged regex hotspots, safer date-space parsing, bounded trailing-token cleanup, and generated test extension source cleanup for hook logging strings.\n- Updated deterministic ID tests to mock `crypto.randomInt` and verified focused suites plus full coverage gate still pass at 100%.\n- Next ship step: open remediation PR and verify CodeQL alert count drops to zero on the PR branch before re-merge."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-06T21:49:05.632Z"}],"before_hash":"dcff41d01c8bceceb7f4438b49ca9686a578a79e806810c33fb1ab1d9c7634df","after_hash":"12adcd6f17096a901ddaa89e525ef5ac6deb5bcbc6741d3d6a15642c3ef6a7a6"}
